# ============================================================
# PERMISSION CORE RUNTIME
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: runtime
domain: permission
scope: permission.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for permission.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers permission visibility,
allow/deny rendering,
delegation-aware display,
historical permission reference,
and safe failure rendering.

## validation_rules
- permission basis must resolve
- actor/resource/action scope must resolve
- delegation scope must resolve
- disclosure scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid permission basis
- invalid scope model
- invalid delegation scope
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish granted/restricted/revoked state,
delegation mode,
historical reference,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- permission runtime scope is explicit
- allow/deny rendering is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
